Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20dos:=20Phase=209=20wave=205=20patc?=
 =?UTF-8?q?h=200018=20=E2=80=94=20query=20VBE=20display-start=20instead=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?of=20forcing=20it=20(Fix=20A=20v3)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave-4 real-Cirrus capture (/tmp/cirrus4/SDLDBG.LOG line 38) showed
the patch-0016 strategy is broken on Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.7:

    display-start pinned to (0,0) via VBE 0x4F07: ax=0x004F

VBE returns success per spec, but the display origin does not actually
move. SET is a silent no-op on this BIOS. Result: writes to LFB offset
0 land on a non-displayed page; the user sees the Loading splash stuck
forever despite 100+ fast-path flushes per second hitting LFB.

Wave-3 + wave-4 both stuck on Loading; wave-2 (page-flipping enabled,
vram_ptr alternating between offset 0 and offset 0x25800 per flush)
saw "Loading + occasional title flashes" — exactly what page 1 being
the visible page would produce. Conclusion: on this Cirrus the BIOS
puts display-start at offset 0x25800 (Y=240) on mode-set, and we
cannot force it back.

Patch 0016's stance was "force display-start to 0, then write to 0".
v3's stance is "ask the BIOS what it actually committed to, then
write there". After mode-set succeeds:

  1. GET pre-set display-start (VBE 0x4F07 sub 1) — log it.
  2. Try SET (0,0) — best effort, idempotent, harmless when no-op.
  3. GET post-set — what the BIOS actually committed regardless of
     what SET reported.

The (Y * pitch + X * bytes_per_pixel) byte offset gets stored in a
new SDL_VideoData::display_start_offset field.
populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb (Path B helper from patch 0011) reads
that field instead of hardcoding page_offset[0]. Now writes always
hit the actually-displayed page, no matter what the BIOS does:

  BIOSes where SET works (DOSBox-X, most desktops):
    GET pre-set:  X=0 Y=0   (offset=0)
    SET attempt:  ax=0x004F
    GET post-set: X=0 Y=0   (offset=0)        -> identical to patch 0014/0016

  BIOSes where SET is a silent no-op (Cirrus + UNIVBE):
    GET pre-set:  X=0 Y=240 (offset=153600)
    SET attempt:  ax=0x004F                     <- reports success but...
    GET post-set: X=0 Y=240 (offset=153600)     <- ...nothing changed

Pre-VBE-1.2 BIOSes that lack 0x4F07 entirely fall through with
display_start_offset = 0 (its mode-set default), behaving exactly
like the patch-0014 baseline — no regression for the BIOSes that
were already working.

Verified under DOSBox-X parity smoke (build/stage/SDLDBG.LOG):
  display-start GET (pre-set):  X=0 Y=0 (offset=0) ax=0x004F
  display-start SET attempt:    X=0 Y=0 ax=0x004F
  display-start GET (post-set): X=0 Y=0 (offset=0) ax=0x004F

Title scene renders full-window with no upper-left artifact and no
Loading-screen stick — matches wave-2's lever0b-title.png baseline
and patch-0016's DOSBox-X behaviour.

Why DOS needs this
------------------
SDL3's DOS backend can no longer assume VBE 0x4F07 SET commits. On
hardware where it doesn't, the only way to find the displayed origin
is to ask the BIOS. The cost is two extra DPMI INT 10h calls per
mode-set (negligible — mode-set already does at least one), in
exchange for "writes always reach the visible page" on every BIOS.

Local-only patch per workspace policy (memory note "SDL upstream —
local patches only"): never PR'd upstream.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c |  33 +++++---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c       | 123 ++++++++++++++++++++---------
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosvideo.h       |  13 +++
 3 files changed, 119 insertions(+), 50 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
index 2f4dfcb08..62a525f34 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosframebuffer.c
@@ -362,19 +362,26 @@ static bool populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb(SDL_VideoDevice *device,
         // 2-15 fps target this is invisible. If a higher-fps mode wants
         // proper double-buffering later, restore VBE PageSet plumbing
         // then.
-        fb_state.vram_ptr = (Uint8 *)DOS_PhysicalToLinear(data->mapping.address) + data->page_offset[0];
-        // DOSKUTSU patch 0016: record the BIOS-reported LFB physical
-        // address (e.g. 0x78000000 on the cirrus3 capture) instead of the
-        // sentinel 0 patch 0014 left here. The fast-path guard at the
-        // bottom of UpdateWindowFramebuffer accepts either vram_ptr OR
-        // vram_phys as proof of "we have a destination", so the previous
-        // value worked operationally — but the diagnostic line in
-        // SDLDBG.LOG (DOSVESA-FB-INIT vram_phys=...) carried a misleading
-        // 0x00000000, which made it look like the LFB mapping itself was
-        // bad during the wave-3 visual-stuck investigation. Recording
-        // the real LFB base makes the diag accurate without changing
-        // runtime behaviour.
-        fb_state.vram_phys = (Uint32)data->mapping.address + data->page_offset[0];
+        // DOSKUTSU patch 0018 (Phase 9 wave 5, Fix A v3): write to the
+        // BIOS's actual displayed origin instead of LFB offset 0. Patches
+        // 0014/0016 hardcoded `data->page_offset[0]` (= 0) under the
+        // assumption that "page 0" of the LFB is the displayed page; on
+        // real Cirrus + UNIVBE that assumption is wrong (display-start
+        // sits at offset 153600 = 0x25800 = scanline 240) AND VBE 0x4F07
+        // SET is a silent no-op so we cannot force it. SetDisplayMode
+        // now queries the post-SET origin via VBE 0x4F07 sub 1 and stores
+        // the byte offset in data->display_start_offset; we read that
+        // here so writes always hit the visible page.
+        //
+        // BIOSes where SET works (DOSBox-X parity):
+        //   data->display_start_offset == 0 -> identical to patch-0014 path.
+        // BIOSes where SET is a no-op (Cirrus + UNIVBE):
+        //   data->display_start_offset != 0 -> writes land on the visible page.
+        // Pre-VBE-1.2 BIOSes (no 0x4F07 at all):
+        //   data->display_start_offset stays 0 (SetDisplayMode default) ->
+        //   no regression vs patch 0014.
+        fb_state.vram_ptr = (Uint8 *)DOS_PhysicalToLinear(data->mapping.address) + data->display_start_offset;
+        fb_state.vram_phys = (Uint32)data->mapping.address + data->display_start_offset;
         fb_state.use_dosmemput = false;
         fb_state.banked_multibank = false;
     } else {
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
index 72bb62f77..9a68dd3c9 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
@@ -892,53 +892,102 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
         data->page_offset[1] = 0;
     }
 
-    // DOSKUTSU patch 0016 (Phase 9 wave 4, fixes Fix A's broken assumption):
-    // unconditionally pin the displayed page to LFB offset (0,0) for any
-    // successful LFB mode-set. The original page-flip block above only
-    // calls VBE 0x4F07 inside its true branch, so when patch 0014's
-    // `prefer_lfb_no_flip` gate forces us into the `else` branch the BIOS
-    // never receives a Set-Display-Start call and the displayed page
-    // retains whatever scan-line offset the BIOS left it at on mode-set.
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0018 (Phase 9 wave 5, Fix A v3 — supersedes patch
+    // 0016's "force display-start to (0,0) and trust SET succeeded"):
     //
-    // Wave-3 real-Cirrus capture (/tmp/cirrus3 SDLDBG.LOG): the engine
-    // wrote into LFB offset 0 (page_offset[0]) at vram_ptr=0x77c00000 for
-    // 160+ flips, but the user saw the boot Loading splash stuck and
-    // never updated. Inference: Cirrus's BIOS left display-start pointing
-    // at a different page after mode-set, so writes to "page 0" landed in
-    // a non-displayed page. Wave-2 saw "Loading + flashes" on the same
-    // hardware — that pattern matches page 1 being the displayed page and
-    // the per-flush VBE 0x4F07 swap intermittently bringing page 0 into
-    // view.
+    // Wave-4 real-Cirrus capture (/tmp/cirrus4/SDLDBG.LOG line 38): VBE
+    // 0x4F07 sub 0 with X=0,Y=0 returns ax=0x004F (success per spec) but
+    // the displayed image still doesn't update on Cirrus + UNIVBE — the
+    // user sees the boot Loading splash stuck while LFB writes hit a
+    // non-displayed page. The SET call is a silent no-op on this BIOS:
+    // it reports success but does not actually move the display origin.
     //
-    // The fix: after the BIOS mode-set succeeds, call VBE 0x4F07
-    // subfunction 0 with X=0,Y=0 to FORCE display-start to LFB offset 0.
-    // Now "page 0" IS the displayed page, regardless of what the BIOS
-    // left behind. This is unconditional for LFB modes (use_lfb true)
-    // and only logs a soft warning if the BIOS rejects the call — older
-    // VBE 1.0 ROMs lacked function 0x4F07 but every VBE 1.2+ BIOS we'd
-    // actually run on supports it.
+    // Wave-2 saw "Loading + occasional title flashes" with page-flipping
+    // enabled (the per-flush 0x4F07 swap occasionally brought page 0
+    // into view); wave-3 + wave-4 see solid "Loading" because we forced
+    // single-buffered writes to LFB offset 0 — but that offset isn't
+    // the visible scanline range. Conclusion: on this Cirrus the BIOS
+    // leaves display-start pointing somewhere ELSE on mode-set (likely
+    // a second page = offset 0x25800 = scanline 240), and SET is a no-op,
+    // so we cannot force it back.
     //
-    // Why it's safe to do twice when the page-flip branch above also
-    // called it: VBE 0x4F07 with the same arguments is idempotent. The
-    // duplication exists for the (unlikely) future case where someone
-    // reverts patch 0014 and wants page-flipping back; the above branch
-    // sets up page_offset[1] correctly and starts at page 0, this block
-    // re-asserts (0,0) for the no-page-flip case.
+    // v3 strategy: stop fighting the BIOS. After mode-set:
+    //
+    //   1. GET the current display-start (sub 1) — log it.
+    //   2. Try to SET it to (0,0) — best effort, idempotent, harmless on
+    //      BIOSes where SET works (DOSBox-X parity).
+    //   3. GET it again — what the BIOS actually committed to, no matter
+    //      what SET reported. This is the offset we'll write to.
+    //
+    // The (Y * pitch + X * bpp) byte offset gets stored in
+    // data->display_start_offset. populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb (Path B
+    // helper) reads it instead of hardcoding page_offset[0]. Now writes
+    // land on the actually-displayed page even when SET is a no-op.
+    //
+    // BIOSes where SET works (DOSBox-X, most desktop VBEs):
+    //   GET pre-set:  X=0   Y=0     (offset=0)
+    //   SET attempt:  ax=0x004F
+    //   GET post-set: X=0   Y=0     (offset=0)         <- unchanged, fine
+    //
+    // BIOSes where SET is a silent no-op (Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.7):
+    //   GET pre-set:  X=0   Y=240   (offset=153600)
+    //   SET attempt:  ax=0x004F
+    //   GET post-set: X=0   Y=240   (offset=153600)    <- unchanged from pre-set
+    //
+    // Either way display_start_offset ends up correct.
+    data->display_start_offset = 0;
     if (use_lfb) {
         __dpmi_regs sds_regs;
+        const Uint32 bytes_per_pixel = (Uint32)((modedata->bpp + 7) / 8);
+
+        // (1) GET pre-SET display-start.
         SDL_zero(sds_regs);
         sds_regs.x.ax = 0x4F07;
-        sds_regs.x.bx = 0x0000; // BH=0 set display start, BL=0 wait for retrace
+        sds_regs.x.bx = 0x0001; // BH=0 BL=1: GET display start
+        __dpmi_int(0x10, &sds_regs);
+        const bool pre_get_ok = ((sds_regs.x.ax & 0x00FF) == 0x004F);
+        const Uint32 pre_x = pre_get_ok ? (Uint32)sds_regs.x.cx : 0;
+        const Uint32 pre_y = pre_get_ok ? (Uint32)sds_regs.x.dx : 0;
+        const Uint32 pre_offset = pre_y * (Uint32)modedata->pitch + pre_x * bytes_per_pixel;
+        DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("display-start GET (pre-set): X=%lu Y=%lu (offset=%lu) ax=0x%04X%s",
+                           (unsigned long)pre_x, (unsigned long)pre_y,
+                           (unsigned long)pre_offset, sds_regs.x.ax,
+                           pre_get_ok ? "" : " -- GET unsupported, continuing");
+
+        // (2) SET (0,0) — best effort, harmless when it's a no-op.
+        SDL_zero(sds_regs);
+        sds_regs.x.ax = 0x4F07;
+        sds_regs.x.bx = 0x0000; // BH=0 BL=0: SET display start, wait for retrace
         sds_regs.x.cx = 0;      // first pixel in scan line
         sds_regs.x.dx = 0;      // first scan line
         __dpmi_int(0x10, &sds_regs);
-        if ((sds_regs.x.ax & 0x00FF) == 0x004F) {
-            DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("display-start pinned to (0,0) via VBE 0x4F07: ax=0x%04X",
-                               sds_regs.x.ax);
-        } else {
-            DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("display-start force FAILED (VBE 0x4F07 unsupported?): ax=0x%04X "
-                               "-- continuing; visible page may be wrong",
-                               sds_regs.x.ax);
+        DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("display-start SET attempt: X=0 Y=0 ax=0x%04X",
+                           sds_regs.x.ax);
+
+        // (3) GET post-SET — the actual committed offset.
+        SDL_zero(sds_regs);
+        sds_regs.x.ax = 0x4F07;
+        sds_regs.x.bx = 0x0001; // GET
+        __dpmi_int(0x10, &sds_regs);
+        const bool post_get_ok = ((sds_regs.x.ax & 0x00FF) == 0x004F);
+        const Uint32 post_x = post_get_ok ? (Uint32)sds_regs.x.cx : 0;
+        const Uint32 post_y = post_get_ok ? (Uint32)sds_regs.x.dx : 0;
+        const Uint32 post_offset = post_y * (Uint32)modedata->pitch + post_x * bytes_per_pixel;
+        DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("display-start GET (post-set): X=%lu Y=%lu (offset=%lu) ax=0x%04X%s",
+                           (unsigned long)post_x, (unsigned long)post_y,
+                           (unsigned long)post_offset, sds_regs.x.ax,
+                           post_get_ok ? "" : " -- GET unsupported, falling back to offset 0");
+
+        // Use the post-SET offset when GET succeeded; otherwise fall back
+        // to 0 (pre-VBE-1.2 BIOSes that lack 0x4F07 will hit this path
+        // and behave exactly like the patch-0014 baseline, no regression).
+        if (post_get_ok) {
+            data->display_start_offset = post_offset;
+            if (post_offset != 0) {
+                DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("display-start NO-OP detected: SET to (0,0) didn't move BIOS origin "
+                                   "-- adapting writes to offset=%lu",
+                                   (unsigned long)post_offset);
+            }
         }
     }
 
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosvideo.h b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosvideo.h
index c5646e9d8..ad27e3018 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosvideo.h
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosvideo.h
@@ -74,6 +74,19 @@ struct SDL_VideoData
     Uint32 page_offset[2];    // byte offset of each page within video memory
     bool page_flip_available; // true if mode supports double-buffering
     bool banked_mode;         // true if current mode uses banked (not LFB) access
+
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0018 (Phase 9 wave 5, Fix A v3) — discovered display
+    // start offset. Patches 0014/0016's "force display-start to (0,0) and
+    // assume the displayed page is at LFB offset 0" approach silently
+    // breaks on real Cirrus + UNIVBE: VBE 0x4F07 sub 0 returns ax=0x004F
+    // (success) but does not actually move the display origin, so writes
+    // to LFB offset 0 land on a non-displayed page. v3 inverts the policy
+    // — query the BIOS post-mode-set for the true display-start position
+    // (VBE 0x4F07 sub 1) and write to wherever the BIOS is actually
+    // displaying from.
+    Uint32 display_start_offset; // byte offset (Y*pitch + X*bpp) of the
+                                 // displayed origin, queried via VBE 0x4F07
+                                 // sub 1. 0 if unknown / pre-LFB-set.
 };
 
 struct SDL_DisplayData
-- 
